net.proteusframework.users.model

Class PrincipalGroupCapability

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.users.capability.AbstractCapability
      • net.proteusframework.users.capability.AbstractDataCapability
        • net.proteusframework.users.capability.AbstractEntityCapability<PrincipalGroup>
          • net.proteusframework.users.model.PrincipalGroupCapability
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Entity<java.lang.Long>, PrincipalGroupGrantableCapability

    @Entity
public class PrincipalGroupCapability
extends AbstractEntityCapability<PrincipalGroup>
implements PrincipalGroupGrantableCapability
    Capability to control the administration of Principal Groups. Consists of a Subject group and a Granted group. The Subject group is the group that may or may not be administered (depending on the isRevocation property) by the Granted group.
    Author:
    Greg Dick
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
